Hi,
Jeffrey A Law:
> It's not strictly correct for any function to assume that specifying "inline"
> will force the function to be inlined.  That may or may not change depending
> on what rth & davem decide to do.
> 
Would it be possible to force egcs to inline all functions declared as
"extern inline"?
Alternately, if we can be sure that any function declared as "static
inline" will never be emitted, that'd fix the problem too. AFAIR this was
not so for some previous versions of GCC.
